paragraph.content:
ammunition for the arms coming within paragraphs (a), (b), (c), (d) and
                        (g) of the definition of
                            arms;

grenades, bombs and other like missiles (whether capable of use with
                        arms or not), and fuses, percussion caps and priming caps
                        therefor;

an air rifle, air gun or air pistol from which any shot, bullet or
                        missile can be discharged with a muzzle energy greater than 2
                        joules;

any portable device which is designed or adapted to stun or disable a
                        person by means of an electric shock applied either with or without direct
                        contact with that person;

any gun, pistol or other propelling or releasing instrument from or by
                        which a projectile containing any gas or chemical could be
                        discharged;

subsection.def:
licensee
                    (持牌人) means a person to whom a licence has
                been granted;

paragraph.content:
any other description of vessel in the waters of Hong Kong not used in
                        navigation or not constructed or adapted for use in navigation;
                        and

at a time or times specified therein tested as to the muzzle energy with
                    which a shot, bullet or other missile could be discharged therefrom;
                    and

subparagraph.content:
such person is found in any vessel, vehicle, train, aircraft, premises or
                    place in which any arms or ammunition or imitation firearm are found;
                    and

arms in terms of paragraph (g) of the definition of
                            arms
                        in that section;
